  "prompt": "What is the difference between gin, vodka, whiskey and rum?",
  "response": "Here are the key differences between these spirits:\n\n1. Gin:\n- Made from grains like wheat or corn\n- Flavored with juniper berries and other botanicals\n- Clear in color\n- Often used in cocktails like martinis and gin & tonics\n\n2. Vodka:\n- Made from grains or potatoes\n- Typically flavorless and colorless\n- Highly distilled\n- Versatile in mixed drinks\n\n3. Whiskey:\n- Made from fermented grain mash (corn, rye, wheat, barley)\n- Aged in wooden barrels\n- Varies in color from light to dark amber\n- Different types: Scotch, Bourbon, Rye, Irish whiskey\n- Usually consumed neat, on the rocks, or in cocktails\n\n4. Rum:\n- Made from sugarcane byproducts like molasses\n- Originates in Caribbean countries\n- Can be light or dark, depending on aging process\n- Usually has a sweeter taste\n- Often used in tropical cocktails like mojitos and daiquiris\n\nThe main differences are in their base ingredients, production methods, flavor profiles, and traditional uses.",
